<p>Ballard and Fremont neighborhoods feature many craftsman-style homes with good roof space for solar installations, while their proximity to Puget Sound provides natural cooling that reduces summer HVAC demands. West Seattle and Beacon Hill offer excellent solar potential due to their elevation and southern exposures, making them ideal for larger 8-10kW systems. The newer construction in South Lake Union and Belltown often includes modern HVAC systems but can benefit significantly from solar additions to offset higher electricity usage in high-rise living situations.</p>

